Theme:  
The Nocturnal Advent 2025: A Chronicle of Shadow and Solstice Light
#NocturnalAdvent2025 

Step into the velvet darkness where Yule magic truly resides. This is not the season of tinsel & commercial cheer, but of ancient frost, sacred rites, & beings who walk the longest night. 

For 31 days, together we will chronicle a tale woven from gothic elegance, pagan roots, & the deep, haunting beauty of the winter solstice. 

Create breathtaking, hyper-detailed visual chapters of a world where witches light candles with whispered spells; where Krampus is not a monster but a necessary judge; & where the returning sun is celebrated with bonfires and blood-oaths.

Weekly Themes

· Week 1: The Awakening Shadow (Dec 1-7): 

The first stirrings of ancient magic. Lighting candles, weaving protective charms, & the arrival of the season's first, formidable heralds.

· Week 2: Echoes of the Old Gods (Dec 8-14): 

The veil thins. Carols for forgotten deities, spectral feasts, & pacts sealed under the sacred mistletoe. The balance between darkness & light is palpable.

· Week 3: The Heart of the Long Night (Dec 15-21): 

The climax of the solstice. The brewing of potent spells, the cracking of secrets, & the vigil for the dark gift-bringer on the longest night.

· Week 4: The Feast of Shadows (Dec 22-28): 
The celebration & its aftermath. The unwrapping of destinies, the grand feast between worlds, & the beginning of poignant farewells.

· Week 5: The Ember's Glow (Dec 29-31): 

The quiet outcome - The release of sacred objects, the final candle, & carrying the season's light into the unknown new year.

Daily Hooks

· Dec 1: A single flame defies the endless night.

· Dec 2: A witch's hands weave a spell of evergreen protection.

· Dec 3: A silent judge prowls, assessing worth not by goodness, but by resilience.

· Dec 4: A letter is sent, but the recipient wears horns, not a fluffy red hat.

· Dec 5: A coven of confectionery and spice dances under a sugar-snow moon.

· Dec 6: Two gifts are left: one of reward, one of consequence.

· Dec 7: A sacred circle is forged from holly, thorn, & feather.

· Dec 8: Their hymns are spells, their breath the runes of winter.

· Dec 9: At the witching hour, the wooden sentinel awakens.

· Dec 10: A blessed brew is stirred to life for the sleeping orchards.

· Dec 11: The laughter of ghosts echoes from a feast long since consumed.

· Dec 12: The sky itself tears open for the passage of the sacred hunt.

· Dec 13: A pact is sealed not with a kiss, but with a drop of blood & magic.

· Dec 14: The forest god returns, his touch making winter itself bloom.

· Dec 15: The kitchen altar: where gingerbread runes hold the future.

· Dec 16: To receive the gift, you must first break the shell.

· Dec 17: The art of wrapping shadows and secrets.

· Dec 18: They dance to burn away the past and summon the sun.

· Dec 19: An angel plays the symphony of the cosmos for a sleeping world.

· Dec 20: The sun is a log, dragged from the woods and brought into the heart of the home.

· Dec 21: A child witnesses the truth of the gift-bringer.

· Dec 22: The box opens to reveal not an object, but a destiny.

· Dec 23: A feast where the guests are as eternal as the stories they tell.

· Dec 24: A dark angel gifts a single, star-like ember to a sleeping child.

· Dec 25: The quiet, blissful peace after the storm of magic.

· Dec 26: Gratitude is delivered on silent, black wings.

· Dec 27: The twin kings of the season part ways at a snowy crossroads.

· Dec 28: A final, ethereal kiss from a love that transcends death.

· Dec 29: The sacred bough is thanked, then returned to the universe in smoke.

· Dec 30: The last light dies, &!from its smoke, the new year is born.

· Dec 31: Standing on the threshold between the past's darkness & the future's mystery.

---

record.text: The article details the critical shift needed: Treating internet-facing edge devices as emergency fixes. If a vendor releases a vulnerability advisory, patch it immediately. Waiting for the next maintenance window is no longer an option.

The key insight: Firewall technology isn't the problem; governance is. Misconfigurations and exposed admin portals are the low-friction targets for modern adversaries. Security teams must prioritize inventory and disable unused services now.
The most overlooked aspect of the AI boom is the environmental cost of stranded assets. We must prioritize sustainable deployment over pure capacity scaling.

We must enforce phishing-resistant MFA across the board. The majority of firewall breaches are facilitated by credential abuse. This single policy change closes the easiest and most-used path for threat actors.
My core recommendation to security leaders: Audit your entire internet-facing inventory today. If you can't account for every exposed interface and patch status, you're relying on luck, not defense.

record.text: The UpIt Google OAuth login has been broken since at least March 26th. As far as I can tell, there is no way to contact them (if they're even still in business).

I tried #MagicPath today. It's a #GenerativeAI service that takes an image you provide and turns it into #VibeCode. In a way, it's an IDE. Output fantastic. Two problems: 1) no code unless you pay, and 2) for a UI generator their UI sucks. Badly. Example: "View" is locked at 50% or 100%. No 88%.

I believe that having 90% of all #GenerativeAI services relying heavily or even exclusively on a #Google OAuth for access is a recipe for disaster. We need a non-partisan IdP credential handshake API for the #AIArt and #AIVideo crowd.

external.description:
Today, AWS announces the AWS MCP Server, a managed remote Model Context Protocol (MCP) server that helps AI agents and AI-native IDEs perform real-world, multi-step tasks across one or more AWS services. The AWS MCP Server consolidates capabilities from the existing AWS API MCP and AWS Knowledge servers into a unified interface, providing access to AWS documentation, generating and executing calls to over 15,000 AWS APIs including those for newly released services, and following pre-built workflows called Agent standard operating procedures (SOPs) that guide AI agents through common tasks on AWS.
 
 With the AWS MCP Server, you can ask AI assistants to perform tasks like hosting static websites on S3, provisioning EC2 instances, troubleshooting Lambda issues, and configuring CloudWatch alarms using Agent SOPs to provide step-by-step guidance. The server handles authentication and authorization through AWS Identity and Access Management (IAM) and provides audit logging through AWS CloudTrail, giving you full control over resources and permissions while enabling AI agents to execute tasks across multiple AWS services helping you complete real-world tasks faster.
 
 The AWS MCP Server is available at no additional cost in the US East (N. Virginia) Region. You pay only for AWS resources you create and applicable data transfer costs. To learn more, see the https://docs.aws.amazon.com/aws-mcp/latest/userguide/understanding-mcp-server-tools.html.

external.description:
Today, AWS announced the expansion of its AWS Resilience Competency program to include Technology Partners, helping customers identify and implement software solutions that enhance the availability and resilience of their critical cloud workloads. This new offering addresses the growing demand for "always on, always available" applications and services.
 
 The AWS Resilience Software Competency validates partner solutions across three essential categories: Design (high availability solutions including proxy and load balancing), Recovery (disaster recovery and data replication), and Operate (continuous resilience through observability and chaos engineering). All participating partners undergo rigorous technical validation by AWS experts to ensure they meet strict performance and operational requirements.
 
 As Werner Vogels, CTO of Amazon, explains: "Everything fails, all the time. With validated and curated solutions from AWS Resilience Partners, customers can achieve in AWS, with a fraction of the cost, a higher system availability they could ever experience if still running critical workloads on-premises." This program follows AWS's shared responsibility model, where AWS manages cloud infrastructure resilience while providing customers with trusted tools and partners to ensure workload resilience.
 
 To get started with the AWS Resilience Software Competency program and browse qualified partners, visit the https://aws.amazon.com/resilience/partners/. Solutions are available through AWS Marketplace for streamlined procurement.
external.title: AWS Launches Resilience Software Competency to help customers build highly available applications

external.description:
Today, AWS Marketplace announces the general availability of variable payments, a new billing option that allows professional services sellers to bill customers as work is delivered. This capability allows sellers to set contract caps and create payment requests throughout project delivery, rather than requiring upfront payment or fixed installment schedules.

 Professional services engagements often involve complexity and uncertainty, making it challenging to accurately scope and price deliverables before work begins. Variable payments supports a flexible engagement approach, while providing transparency and control for buyers. AWS Marketplace Sellers can create private offers for professional services and utilize variable payments to bill up to a predetermined contract maximum. This allows sellers to bill in AWS Marketplace based on outcomes, as milestones are completed, or as time and materials are consumed. Throughout the engagement, sellers create payment requests that describe deliverables and specify milestones or time and materials. Customers receive email notifications and can review and approve each request manually, or enable auto-approval for streamlined processing.

 To learn more, visit the https://docs.aws.amazon.com/marketplace/latest/userguide/proserv-variable-payments.html, or access the https://aws.amazon.com/marketplace/management/offers/ to create a professional services private offer with variable payment.
